Using NGHELP (Norton Guide Help) is very simple.
At the dos prompt type: NGHELP
(see history below for command options)
Now it will remain in memory until you choice to UnInstall it.
To activate NGHELP press LeftShift+F1. If a file named 'NGHELP.INI' is in the 
directory where NGCL.EXE resides (only for Dos 3.0 and higher otherwhise NGHELP
searches the PATH for this file) , then NGHELP popups with the NG file when you 
last saved NGHELP.INI.

When no NG file is active you can go to the menu wich is called Options. 
Press return when the Database is highlighted. NGHELP looks in the current 
directory if NGHELP.INI is not available otherwhise in the directory which is 
saved in NGHELP.INI for the NG files. When NG files are available it popups
with a menu. Press return, NGHELP will now load the information containing 
the choisen NG file.

Keys who are used :
LeftShift-F1  Activate NGHELP
Esc           Quit/Go down one level
Return        Activate Somthing
PageDown/PageUp,Cursor Down/Up/Left/Right move when apropiate through the text
F9            Larg/Small window


